\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces Attestix Protocol module architecture (native LaTeX/TikZ rendering). The four domain projects (top) each instantiate the parameterised \texttt  {AttestixManager} from \texttt  {shared/attestix\_client.py}, which wraps the nine service modules in the pip-installed \texttt  {attestix} package. All cryptographic artefacts are persisted to the local JSON store under \texttt  {\textasciitilde /.attestix/}. The security middleware intercepts agent calls flowing from the five orchestration frameworks at the bottom.}}{14}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{3.1}{14}{Attestix Protocol module architecture (native LaTeX/TikZ rendering). The four domain projects (top) each instantiate the parameterised \texttt {AttestixManager} from \texttt {shared/attestix\_client.py}, which wraps the nine service modules in the pip-installed \texttt {attestix} package. All cryptographic artefacts are persisted to the local JSON store under \texttt {\textasciitilde /.attestix/}. The security middleware intercepts agent calls flowing from the five orchestration frameworks at the bottom}{figure.caption.13}{}}
